text: I'm definitely late to the party here, but let me just point out that materials like Kevlar, AKA aramid fiber, are both flexible and tough. Toughness refers to the ability to absorb energy before fracture, while flexibility refers to the ability to deflection in proportion to force applied. Just saying.
